<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ PARIS _ The Georges Pompidou Center, known to
the French as Beauborg because the French don't want to call things
and places by the same name as the rest of us, is a museum where an
old auto transmission _ among other things _ is considered art.
(Kleinberg, Cox News Service.) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG _ Mr Pibb? This cannot be so. My son and Dr Pepper have
been linked almost since birth, sharing the same birthplace: Waco.
Before he could bite off ``c's'' and ``t's'' he was requesting
Dopper Pepper. Waco being the nation's per-capita Dr Pepper
consumption capital, he was contributing to the cause almost before
he consented to solid food. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald). 12. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ My son has a saying: ``When
Momma ain't happy, ain't nobody happy.'' It's not original _ I
think he read it on a tee shirt in Myrtle Beach _ but it's true and
right now, Momma ain't too happy. The day got off to a bad start
about two this morning when a sudden north wind blasted me out of
my summer sleeping habit _ a Pawley's Island hammock on an upstairs
screened porch. Blew the comforters right off me and whipped the
bamboo wind chimes into a frenzy. Freaky weather, I grumbled as I
picked up the cat and made my way inside. She grumbled too.
(Schuett, Cox News Service). MOVED
