<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   COURT-RIVER (Washington) _ Stepping into a territorial deal
dating to 1632, the Supreme Court agrees to referee a dispute
between Virginia and Maryland over the Potomac River. The court
also may be called on to resolve water disputes involving seven
other states _ California, Florida, Alabama, Arizona, Georgia,
Kansas and Nebraska. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington)- A federal judge in Texas is defiantly
trying to do what Republicans in Congress could not _ block modern
meat inspection methods that protect the health of consumers. The
judge ruled that the Agriculture Department had no authority to
penalize a processing plant that failed three tests for salmonella
under new scientific standards approved in 1995. If the judge's
ruling stands, the whole country could be in danger. By MARIANNE
MEANS
</P>
</TEXT>
