experience without swim tests or macrame projects. The camps focus
on environmental workshops and outdoor adventure. ``We've designed
our programs so that there is truly something for everyone,'' said
Seth Benz, director of the Maine Audubon camp. ``Audubon camps
offer a wealth of activities that nature enthusiasts of all levels,
and interests will find deeply rewarding. People leave our camp
with a new sense of wonder about the world around them.'' Weeklong
sessions are held at camps in Maine, Wyoming, Minnesota,
Connecticut, and Wisconsin from June to September. For more
information, call 888-404-7743 for camps in Connecticut, Minnesota,
or Wyoming; 888-325-5261 for Maine; and 715-635-6543 for Wisconsin;
or visit www.audubon.org/educate/cw.
