<P>
   WINE-TALK (Undated) _ The Wine Talk Column: So powerful a force
are Duboeuf wines in the Beaujolais market, and so distinctive is
their style, that most wine drinkers assume that all Beaujolais
tastes like Georges Duboeuf's ubiquitous Beaujolais-Villages. That
assumption is not far from wrong. By Frank J. Prial.
