   MARIJUANA-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Grass,'' director Ron Mann's
punchy and enjoyable new documentary on the history of marijuana in
the U.S. during the 20th century, begins with the creation of
marijuana as a part of institutionalized racism, starting with laws
invented to make the substance illegal in the Southwest as a way of
persecuting Mexicans. Reviewed by Elvis Mitchell.
</P>
