block modern meat inspection methods that protect the health of
consumers. The judge ruled that the Agriculture Department had no
authority to penalize a processing plant that failed three tests
for salmonella under new scientific standards approved in 1995. If
the judge's ruling stands, the whole country could be in danger. By
MARIANNE MEANS.
