including Ted Turner and Gerald Levin, convene today at the CNN
World Report Conference. Coverage of conference and remarks by
Turner and Levin. (Kempner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-SUIT _ ATLANTA _ Following today's developments including
postponement of important class certification brief and a protest
outside Coke's Atlanta headquarters. (Unger, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   NCR-BOOK _ NCR is usually considered a company of metal and
machines, not Cheddar Mac Salad and Petite Apple Tarts. Local
historian Curt Dalton has put together a book that probably won't
change that, but ``Delicious Recipes and Food for Thought'' goes
far to shed light on the character of John H. Patterson, NCR's
founder, a socially conscious businessman whose activism found
outlets in some unusual but effective ways. (Dayton Daily News)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Eds. Also MOVED in the Lifestyle (l) category
</P>
<P>
   DOW _ Investors returned to the stock market after the Memorial
Day holiday in a buying mood, hopeful if not confident that this
week's important economic news will favor the market. The first
major item _ the consumer confidence index _ took an unexpectedly
strong jump higher, which buoyed investors who were concerned that
the economy might slump enough to hurt corporate profits. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DEPOT-EXPO _ Home Depot has identified Chicago, New York and Los
Angeles as expansion markets for its Expo Design Center rollout. As
previously reported, HD plans to have 200 Expos by 2005. It
currently has 15. Also, Sears recently announced it would speed up
the expansion of its Great Indoors chain, which tries to mimic
Expo. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
