   LEDE STORY:
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ The Nasdaq composite index surged to the
biggest gain in its 29-year history on Tuesday, as investors
snapped up technology stocks. The performance of the Nasdaq was the
highlight of a very strong session for stocks generally. ``This
could be the start of something good,'' said Bill Allyn, head of
listed trading at Jefferies &AMP; Co. But despite the positives and the
possibility of an impending summer rally, there are some caveats.
This was the first day following a long weekend, and trading
volume, a good gauge of investor enthusiasm, was fairly light. And
the gains were recorded without a great deal of market-moving news
developments.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 8 p.m.)
</P>
