athletic apparel maker Champion, to focus on food and beverages,
intimates, and household products. By David Barboza.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 8:30 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   BOTTOM CENTER:
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-INSURANCE (Shanghai) _ Sy Sternberg, the chairman of New
York Life Insurance, was in China this week trying to figure out
whom to meet so as to ensure that his company is next among the
dozens of insurers who have applied for a license to do business in
China. In China's murky business world, where market access depends
on whom you know and how happy you have made them _ though no one
will tell you who those people are. Instead, chief executives like
Sternberg operate on supposition and hearsay to identify the hidden
decision makers and cultivate ``top of mind,'' which means making
their company the first that Chinese leaders think of when
considering foreign supplicants from their industry. By Craig S.
Smith.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 8:30 p.m.)
</P>
