 PERSONALS: The Cases of the Disappearing Mayonnaise  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   In Champaign, Ill., the theft of a trailer loaded with $20,000
worth of Kraft mayonnaise was cause for that town's newspaper, the
News-Gazette, to survey recent incidents of food theft in the
Champaign area. Personals is indebted to  &UR; J. Ehrlich &LR;  for passing
along the story. Among the crimes:
</P>
