<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
WILDFIRE (Phoenix) - Arizona Gov. Jane Hull warns that the kind of
wildfires that have plagued New Mexico will happen in Arizona this
summer, a tinderbox waiting to ignite. The national forests in
Arizona may do massive closures beginning June 7. That concept is
under consideration and might include all of the state's Rim
forests. By JUDD SLIVKA. Story will move in the `A` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
LIDDY (Undated) - Spend any time at all with Tom Liddy, one of four
Republicans scrambling for a foothold in the race for the 1st
Congressional District, and you quickly realize that his father,
former Watergate figure G. Gordon Liddy, is never far from his
side. Perhaps not literally. But there he is in the photographs in
the candidate's Tempe campaign office, standing next to family
friend Waylon Jennings.
