<HEADLINE>
SPARKS OPEN AGAINST UTAH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PAMELA LEWIS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ The Los Angeles Sparks and Utah Starzz
closed the regular season together last year and open the 2000
season together at 7:30 tonight at the Forum.
</P>
<P>
   The Starzz defeated the Sparks, 89-81, to end their season at
15-19, while Los Angeles advanced to the playoffs with a 21-12
mark.
</P>
<P>
   Center Lisa Leslie, guard Tamecka Dixon and swing player Mwadi
Mabika begin their fourth season with the Sparks. All three will be
on the floor along with forward DeLisha Milton and point guard
Ukari Figgs.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks lead the series with Utah, 8-4, and are 5-1 at home.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps the tallest starting squad in the league, Utah is led by
6-2 Natalie Williams (18.0 points, 9.1 rebounds), 7-2 Margo Dydek
(12.6 ppg, 6.3 rpg), 6-1 LaTanya Johnson (6.5 ppg), 6-0 guard
Adrienne Goodson (14.9 ppg, 2.7 assists) and 5-9 guard Korie Hlede
(9.8 ppg). Starzz point guard Jennifer Azzi underwent hand surgery
last week and is expected to return in late June.
</P>
