<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, MAY 31
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-DOCTORS-ONLINE-NYT (moved on Monday, May 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 29,
about Web sites that help doctors with diagnoses and provide
immediate answers to questions from patients omitted the given name
of a pulmonary specialist in Palo Alto, Calif., who uses the sites.
He is Dr. Andy Newman.
</P>
<P>
   BC-PERU-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Monday, May 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 29,
about American officials' criticism of the presidential election in
Peru on Sunday misstated the site of a report from election
observers to the Organization of American States set for today. It
is in Washington; the organization is to meet in Canada next week
and will also discuss the issue there.
</P>
<P>
   BC-AUSTRALIA-CIVIL-RIGHTS-NYT (moved on Sunday, May 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, May 28,
about a demonstration in Sydney in support of social justice for
Australia's black minority misstated the city's population. It is
four million, not eight million.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
