<P>
   (NYT1) BRAY, England -- May 30, 2000 -- BRITAIN-FOOD-SCIENCE-1
-- Heston Blumenthal, bottom, runs the Fat Duck, a restaurant in
this idyllic village on the Thames, 35 miles west of London, where
science joins art in the endless search for better flavor.
Blumenthal has allied himself with Peter Barham, top, a 49-year-old
physicist at the University of Bristol, with remarkable results. In
only a few years, the Duck has waddled to the top of several lists
of England's best restaurants. (Jonathan Player/The New York Times)
