<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-PHILLIPS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PHILLIPS LANDS IN JAIL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRANK C. GIRARDOT  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Troubled former professional football player
Lawrence Phillips landed in the Beverly Hills jail over the holiday
weekend on suspicion of beating his girlfriend, authorities said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   A graduate of Baldwin Park High School, Phillips, 25, is
scheduled for arraignment this morning in the Beverly Hills branch
of Los Angeles County court. He is being held on $500,000 bail and
suspected of domestic violence and carrying a concealed weapon. If
convicted he could face time in state prison, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Police did not identify the victim. Phillips remains in custody
in the Beverly Hills jail.
</P>
<P>
   ``Officers responded to a call of domestic violence in the 9000
block of Burton Way at 4:15 a.m. Saturday morning,'' said Beverly
Hills police Lt. Ed Kreins. ``The victim, age 25, identified
herself as Phillips' girlfriend. She declined medical treatment but
was given first aid by officers on the scene.''
</P>
<P>
   Phillips was not at the residence when officers arrived for the
initial call, Kreins said.
</P>
<P>
   ``When the officers got there the suspect was not there,''
Kreins said. ``At that time they identified the suspect as Lawrence
Phillips.''
</P>
<P>
   Police officers were again called to the scene several hours
later. Phillips was arrested at that time, Kreins said. He was
taken into custody without incident.
</P>
<P>
   A spokeswoman for Los Angeles County District Attorney Gil
Garcetti said Tuesday that his office was not familiar with the
particulars of the case.
</P>
<P>
   Phillips, who grew up in a West Covina group home, has had
several brushes with the law. While a student at the University of
Nebraska, he was arrested on suspicion of assaulting his
girlfriend. In subsequent years he has been arrested for driving
under the influence and battery in separate cases.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-30-00 2336EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
